datastore_version_id.Description: ID of the version of the data store.

min.Description: Minimum value of a configuration parameter.

vkcs_db_datastores.Description: Use this data source to get a list of datastores from VKCS. **New since v.0.2.0**.

id.Description: The id of the datastore.

name.Description: Name of the datastore.

region.Description: The `region` to fetch availability zones from, defaults to the provider's `region`

vkcs_db_instance.Description: Use this data source to get the information on a db instance resource.

backup_schedule.Description: Object that represents configuration of PITR backup. This functionality is available only for postgres datastore. **New since v.0.1.4**.

start_minutes.Description: Minutes part of timestamp of initial backup.

vkcs_db_user.Description: Use this data source to get the information on a db user resource.

databases.Description: List of names of the databases, that user is created for.

host.Description: IP address of the host that user will be accessible from.

id.Description: The id of the user in form "dbms_id/user_name".

vkcs_images_image.Description: Use this data source to get the ID of an available VKCS image.

checksum.Description: The checksum of the data associated with the image.

container_format.Description: The format of the image's container.

created_at.Description: The date the image was created.

disk_format.Description: The format of the image's disk.

file.Description: The trailing path after the endpoint that represent the location of the image or the path to retrieve it.

member_status.Description: Status for adding a new member (tenant) to an image member list.

metadata.Description: The metadata associated with the image. Image metadata allow for meaningfully define the image properties and tags. See https://docs.openstack.org/glance/latest/user/metadefs-concepts.html.

min_disk_gb.Description: The minimum amount of disk space required to use the image.

min_ram_mb.Description: The minimum amount of ram required to use the image.

most_recent.Description: If more than one result is returned, use the most recent image.

name.Description: The name of the image.

properties.Description: A map of key/value pairs to match an image with. All specified properties must be matched. Unlike other options filtering by `properties` does by client on the result of search query. Filtering is applied if server response contains at least 2 images. In case there is only one image the `properties` ignores.

protected.Description: Whether or not the image is protected.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Image client. An Image client is needed to create an Image that can be used with a compute instance. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used.

schema.Description: The path to the JSON-schema that represent the image or image

size_bytes.Description: The size of the image (in bytes).

size_max.Description: The maximum size (in bytes) of the image to return.

size_min.Description: The minimum size (in bytes) of the image to return.

tag.Description: Search for images with a specific tag.

tags.Description: The tags list of the image.

updated_at.Description: The date the image was last updated.

visibility.Description: The visibility of the image. Must be one of "private", "community", or "shared". Defaults to "private".

acl.Description: The list of ACLs assigned to a container.

secret_refs.Description: A set of dictionaries containing references to secrets.

updated_at.Description: The date the container was last updated.

Use this data source to get the ID and the payload of an available Key secret

updated_at.Description: The date the secret was last updated.

updated_at_filter.Description: Date filter to select the Secret with updated matching the specified criteria. See Date Filters below for more detail.

user_id.Description: The user of the cluster template.

volume_driver.Description: The name of the driver that is used for the volumes of the cluster nodes.

vkcs_compute_instance.Description:
Manages a compute VM instance resource.

~> **Note:** All arguments including the instance admin password will be stored in the raw state as plain-text. [Read more about sensitive data in state](https://www.terraform.io/docs/language/state/sensitive-data.html).

access_ip_v4.Description: The first detected Fixed IPv4 address.

admin_pass.Description: The administrative password to assign to the server. Changing this changes the root password on the existing server.

all_metadata.Description: Contains all instance metadata, even metadata not set by Terraform.

all_tags.Description: The collection of tags assigned on the instance, which have been explicitly and implicitly added.

availability_zone.Description: The availability zone in which to create the server. Conflicts with `availability_zone_hints`. Changing this creates a new server.

block_device.Description: Configuration of block devices. The block_device structure is documented below. Changing this creates a new server. You can specify multiple block devices which will create an instance with multiple disks. This configuration is very flexible, so please see the following [reference](https://docs.openstack.org/nova/latest/user/block-device-mapping.html) for more information.

boot_index.Description: The boot index of the volume. It defaults to 0. Changing this creates a new server.

delete_on_termination.Description: Delete the volume / block device upon termination of the instance. Defaults to false. Changing this creates a new server.

destination_type.Description: The type that gets created. Possible values are "volume" and "local". Changing this creates a new server.

device_type.Description: The low-level device type that will be used. Most common thing is to leave this empty. Changing this creates a new server.

disk_bus.Description: The low-level disk bus that will be used. Most common thing is to leave this empty. Changing this creates a new server.

guest_format.Description: Specifies the guest server disk file system format, such as `ext2`, `ext3`, `ext4`, `xfs` or `swap`. Swap block device mappings have the following restrictions: source_type must be blank and destination_type must be local and only one swap disk per server and the size of the swap disk must be less than or equal to the swap size of the flavor. Changing this creates a new server.

source_type.Description: The source type of the device. Must be one of "blank", "image", "volume", or "snapshot". Changing this creates a new server.

uuid.Description: (Optional if `source_type` is set to `"blank"` ) The UUID of the image, volume, or snapshot. Changing this creates a new server.

volume_size.Description: The size of the volume to create (in gigabytes). Required in the following combinations: source=image and destination=volume, source=blank and destination=local, and source=blank and destination=volume. Changing this creates a new server.

volume_type.Description: The volume type that will be used. Changing this creates a new server.

config_drive.Description: Whether to use the config_drive feature to configure the instance. Changing this creates a new server.

flavor_id.Description: (Required if `flavor_name` is empty) The flavor ID of the desired flavor for the server. Changing this resizes the existing server.

flavor_name.Description: (Required if `flavor_id` is empty) The name of the desired flavor for the server. Changing this resizes the existing server.

force_delete.Description: Whether to force the compute instance to be forcefully deleted. This is useful for environments that have reclaim / soft deletion enabled.

image_id.Description: (Required if `image_name` is empty and not booting from a volume. Do not specify if booting from a volume.) The image ID of the desired image for the server. Changing this creates a new server.

image_name.Description: (Required if `image_id` is empty and not booting from a volume. Do not specify if booting from a volume.) The name of the desired image for the server. Changing this creates a new server.

key_pair.Description: The name of a key pair to put on the server. The key pair must already be created and associated with the tenant's account. Changing this creates a new server.

metadata.Description: Metadata key/value pairs to make available from within the instance. Changing this updates the existing server metadata.

name.Description: A unique name for the resource.

network.Description: An array of one or more networks to attach to the instance. The network object structure is documented below. Changing this creates a new server.

access_network.Description: Specifies if this network should be used for provisioning access. Accepts true or false. Defaults to false.

fixed_ip_v4.Description: Specifies a fixed IPv4 address to be used on this network. Changing this creates a new server.

mac.Description: The MAC address of the NIC on that network.

name.Description: (Optional if `uuid` or `port` is provided) The human-readable name of the network. Changing this creates a new server.

port.Description: (Optional if `uuid` or `name` is provided) The port UUID of a network to attach to the server. Changing this creates a new server.

uuid.Description: (Optional if `port`  or `name` is provided) The network UUID to attach to the server. Changing this creates a new server.

network_mode.Description: Special string for `network` option to create the server. `network_mode` can be `"auto"` or `"none"`. Please see the following [reference](https://docs.openstack.org/api-ref/compute/?expanded=create-server-detail#id11) for more information. Conflicts with `network`.

personality.Description: Customize the personality of an instance by defining one or more files and their contents. The personality structure is described below.

content.Description: The contents of the file. Limited to 255 bytes.

file.Description: The absolute path of the destination file.

power_state.Description: Provide the VM state. Only 'active' and 'shutoff' are supported values. *Note*: If the initial power_state is the shutoff the VM will be stopped immediately after build and the provisioners like remote-exec or files are not supported.

region.Description: The region in which to create the server instance. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new server.

scheduler_hints.Description: Provide the Nova scheduler with hints on how the instance should be launched. The available hints are described below.

group.Description: A UUID of a Server Group. The instance will be placed into that group.

security_groups.Description: An array of one or more security group names to associate with the server. Changing this results in adding/removing security groups from the existing server. *Note*: When attaching the instance to networks using Ports, place the security groups on the Port and not the instance. *Note*: Names should be used and not ids, as ids trigger unnecessary updates.

stop_before_destroy.Description: Whether to try stop instance gracefully before destroying it, thus giving chance for guest OS daemons to stop correctly. If instance doesn't stop within timeout, it will be destroyed anyway.

tags.Description: A set of string tags for the instance. Changing this updates the existing instance tags.

user_data.Description: The user data to provide when launching the instance.	Changing this creates a new server.

vendor_options.Description: Map of additional vendor-specific options. Supported options are described below.

detach_ports_before_destroy.Description: Whether to try to detach all attached ports to the vm before destroying it to make sure the port state is correct after the vm destruction. This is helpful when the port is not deleted.

ignore_resize_confirmation.Description: Boolean to control whether to ignore manual confirmation of the instance resizing.

vkcs_compute_interface_attach.Description: Attaches a Network Interface (a Port) to an Instance using the VKCS Compute API.

fixed_ip.Description:
An IP address to assosciate with the port.
_NOTE_: This option cannot be used with port_id. You must specify a network_id. The IP address must lie in a range on the supplied network.

instance_id.Description: The ID of the Instance to attach the Port or Network to.

network_id.Description:
The ID of the Network to attach to an Instance. A port will be created automatically.
_NOTE_: This option and `port_id` are mutually exclusive.

port_id.Description:
The ID of the Port to attach to an Instance.
_NOTE_: This option and `network_id` are mutually exclusive.

region.Description: The region in which to create the interface attachment. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new attachment.

vkcs_compute_keypair.Description:
Manages a keypair resource within VKCS.

~> **Important Security Notice** The private key generated by this resource will be stored *unencrypted* in your Terraform state file. **Use of this resource for production deployments is *not* recommended**. Instead, generate a private key file outside of Terraform and distribute it securely to the system where Terraform will be run.

fingerprint.Description: The fingerprint of the public key.

name.Description: A unique name for the keypair. Changing this creates a new keypair.

private_key.Description: The generated private key when no public key is specified.

public_key.Description: A pregenerated OpenSSH-formatted public key. Changing this creates a new keypair. If a public key is not specified, then a public/private key pair will be automatically generated. If a pair is created, then destroying this resource means you will lose access to that keypair forever.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Compute client. Keypairs are associated with accounts, but a Compute client is needed to create one. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new keypair.

members.Description: The instances that are part of this server group.

policies.Description: The set of policies for the server group. All policies are mutually exclusive. See the Policies section for more information. Changing this creates a new server group.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Compute client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new server group.

instance_id.Description: The ID of the Instance to attach the Volume to.

volume_id.Description: The ID of the Volume to attach to an Instance.

vkcs_images_image.Description:
Manages an Image resource within VKCS.

~> **Note:** All arguments including the source image URL password will be stored in the raw state as plain-text. [Read more about sensitive data in state](https://www.terraform.io/docs/language/state/sensitive-data.html).

checksum.Description: The checksum of the data associated with the image.

container_format.Description: The container format. Must be one of "bare".

created_at.Description: The date the image was created.

disk_format.Description: The disk format. Must be one of "raw", "iso".

file.Description: The trailing path after the image endpoint that represent the location of the image or the path to retrieve it.

image_cache_path.Description: This is the directory where the images will be downloaded. Images will be stored with a filename corresponding to the url's md5 hash. Defaults to "$HOME/.terraform/image_cache"

image_source_password.Description: The password of basic auth to download `image_source_url`.

image_source_url.Description: This is the url of the raw image. The image will be downloaded in the `image_cache_path` before being uploaded to VKCS. Conflicts with `local_file_path`.

image_source_username.Description: The username of basic auth to download `image_source_url`.

local_file_path.Description: This is the filepath of the raw image file that will be uploaded to VKCS. Conflicts with `image_source_url`

metadata.Description: The metadata associated with the image. Image metadata allow for meaningfully define the image properties and tags. See https://docs.openstack.org/glance/latest/user/metadefs-concepts.html.

min_disk_gb.Description: Amount of disk space (in GB) required to boot image. Defaults to 0.

min_ram_mb.Description: Amount of ram (in MB) required to boot image. Defauts to 0.

name.Description: The name of the image.

owner.Description: The id of the vkcs user who owns the image.

properties.Description: A map of key/value pairs to set freeform information about an image. See the "Notes" section for further information about properties.

protected.Description: If true, image will not be deletable. Defaults to false.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Image client. An Image client is needed to create an Image that can be used with a compute instance. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new Image.

schema.Description: The path to the JSON-schema that represent the image or image

size_bytes.Description: The size in bytes of the data associated with the image.

status.Description: The status of the image. It can be "queued", "active" or "saving".

tags.Description: The tags of the image. It must be a list of strings. At this time, it is not possible to delete all tags of an image.

updated_at.Description: The date the image was last updated.

verify_checksum.Description: If false, the checksum will not be verified once the image is finished uploading.

visibility.Description: The visibility of the image. Must be one of "private", "community", or "shared". The ability to set the visibility depends upon the configuration of the VKCS cloud.

vkcs_keymanager_container.Description: Manages a key container resource within VKCS.

acl.Description: Allows to control an access to a container. Currently only the `read` operation is supported. If not specified, the container is accessible project wide. The `read` structure is described below.

created_at.Description: The date the container ACL was created.

project_access.Description: Whether the container is accessible project wide. Defaults to `true`.

updated_at.Description: The date the container ACL was last updated.

users.Description: The list of user IDs, which are allowed to access the container, when `project_access` is set to `false`.

consumers.Description: The list of the container consumers. The structure is described below.

name.Description: The name of the consumer.

container_ref.Description: The container reference / where to find the container.

created_at.Description: The date the container ACL was created.

name.Description: Human-readable name for the Container. Does not have to be unique.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the KeyManager client. A KeyManager client is needed to create a container. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new container.

secret_refs.Description: A set of dictionaries containing references to secrets. The structure is described below.

name.Description: The name of the secret reference. The reference names must correspond the container type, more details are available [here](https://docs.openstack.org/barbican/stein/api/reference/containers.html).

secret_ref.Description: The secret reference / where to find the secret, URL.

type.Description: Used to indicate the type of container. Must be one of `generic`, `rsa` or `certificate`.

updated_at.Description: The date the container ACL was last updated.

vkcs_keymanager_secret.Description:
Manages a key secret resource within VKCS.

~> **Important Security Notice** The payload of this resource will be stored *unencrypted* in your Terraform state file. **Use of this resource for production deployments is *not* recommended**. [Read more about sensitive data in state](https://www.terraform.io/docs/language/state/sensitive-data.html).

acl.Description: Allows to control an access to a secret. Currently only the `read` operation is supported. If not specified, the secret is accessible project wide.

created_at.Description: The date the container ACL was created.

project_access.Description: Whether the container is accessible project wide. Defaults to `true`.

updated_at.Description: The date the container ACL was last updated.

users.Description: The list of user IDs, which are allowed to access the container, when `project_access` is set to `false`.

algorithm.Description: Metadata provided by a user or system for informational purposes.

all_metadata.Description: The map of metadata, assigned on the secret, which has been explicitly and implicitly added.

bit_length.Description: Metadata provided by a user or system for informational purposes.

content_types.Description: The map of the content types, assigned on the secret.

created_at.Description: The date the secret ACL was created.

expiration.Description: The expiration time of the secret in the RFC3339 timestamp format (e.g. `2019-03-09T12:58:49Z`). If omitted, a secret will never expire. Changing this creates a new secret.

mode.Description: Metadata provided by a user or system for informational purposes.

name.Description: Human-readable name for the Secret. Does not have to be unique.

payload.Description: The secret's data to be stored. **payload\_content\_type** must also be supplied if **payload** is included.

payload_content_encoding.Description: (required if **payload** is encoded) The encoding used for the payload to be able to include it in the JSON request. Must be either `base64` or `binary`.

payload_content_type.Description: (required if **payload** is included) The media type for the content of the payload. Must be one of `text/plain`, `text/plain;charset=utf-8`, `text/plain; charset=utf-8`, `application/octet-stream`, `application/pkcs8`.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the KeyManager client. A KeyManager client is needed to create a secret. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new V1 secret.

secret_ref.Description: The secret reference / where to find the secret.

secret_type.Description: Used to indicate the type of secret being stored. For more information see [Secret types](https://docs.openstack.org/barbican/latest/api/reference/secret_types.html).

updated_at.Description: The date the secret ACL was last updated.

vkcs_kubernetes_cluster.Description: Provides a kubernetes cluster resource. This can be used to create, modify and delete kubernetes clusters.

cluster_template_id.Description: The UUID of the Kubernetes cluster template. It can be obtained using the cluster_template data source.

created_at.Description: The time at which cluster was created.

dns_domain.Description: Custom DNS cluster domain. Changing this creates a new cluster.

ingress_floating_ip.Description: Floating IP created for ingress service.

insecure_registries.Description: Addresses of registries from which you can download images without checking certificates. Changing this creates a new cluster.

keypair.Description: The name of the Compute service SSH keypair. Changing this creates a new cluster.

labels.Description:
The list of optional key value pairs representing additional properties of the cluster. Changing this creates a new cluster.

  * `calico_ipv4pool` to set subnet where pods will be created. Default 10.100.0.0/16.
  * `clean_volumes` to remove pvc volumes when deleting a cluster. Default False.
  * `cloud_monitoring` to enable cloud monitoring feature.
  * `docker_registry_enabled=true` to preinstall Docker Registry.
  * `etcd_volume_size` to set etcd volume size. Default 10Gb.
  * `ingress_controller="nginx"` to preinstall NGINX Ingress Controller.
  * `kube_log_level` to set log level for kubelet in range 0 to 8.
  * `master_volume_size` to set master vm volume size. Default 50Gb.
  * `cluster_node_volume_type` to set master vm volume type. Default ceph-hdd.
  * `prometheus_monitoring=true` to preinstall monitoring system based on Prometheus and Grafana.

loadbalancer_subnet_id.Description: The UUID of the load balancer's subnet. Changing this creates new cluster.

master_addresses.Description: IP addresses of the master node of the cluster.

master_count.Description: The number of master nodes for the cluster. Changing this creates a new cluster.

master_flavor.Description: The UUID of a flavor for the master nodes. If master_flavor is not present, value from cluster_template will be used.

name.Description: The name of the cluster. Changing this creates a new cluster. Should match the pattern `^[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_.-]*$`.

pods_network_cidr.Description: Network cidr of k8s virtual network

region.Description: Region to use for the cluster. Default is a region configured for provider.

stack_id.Description: UUID of the Orchestration service stack.

status.Description: Current state of a cluster. Changing this to `RUNNING` or `SHUTOFF` will turn cluster on/off.

updated_at.Description: The time at which cluster was created.

vkcs_kubernetes_node_group.Description: Provides a cluster node group resource. This can be used to create, modify and delete cluster's node group.

autoscaling_enabled.Description: Determines whether the autoscaling is enabled.

availability_zones.Description:
The list of availability zones of the node group. Zones `MS1` and  `GZ1` are available. By default, node group is being created at cluster's zone.
**Important:** Receiving default AZ add it manually to your main.tf config to sync it with state to avoid node groups force recreation in the future.

cluster_id.Description: The UUID of the existing cluster.

created_at.Description: The time at which node group was created.

flavor_id.Description: The flavor UUID of this node group.

labels.Description: The list of objects representing representing additional properties of the node group. Each object should have attribute "key". Object may also have optional attribute "value".

max_node_unavailable.Description: The maximum number of nodes that can fail during an upgrade. The default value is 25 percent.

max_nodes.Description: The maximum allowed nodes for this node group.

min_nodes.Description: The minimum allowed nodes for this node group. Default to 0 if not set.

name.Description: The name of node group to create. Changing this will force to create a new node group.

node_count.Description: The node count for this node group. Should be greater than 0. If `autoscaling_enabled` parameter is set, this attribute will be ignored during update.

state.Description: Determines current state of node group (RUNNING, SHUTOFF, ERROR).

taints.Description: The list of objects representing node group taints. Each object should have following attributes: key, value, effect.

updated_at.Description: The time at which node group was created.

uuid.Description: The UUID of the cluster's node group.

volume_size.Description: The size in GB for volume to load nodes from. Changing this will force to create a new node group.

volume_type.Description: The volume type to load nodes from. Changing this will force to create a new node group.

vkcs_lb_l7policy.Description: Manages a Load Balancer L7 Policy resource within VKCS.

action.Description: The L7 Policy action - can either be REDIRECT\_TO\_POOL, REDIRECT\_TO\_URL or REJECT.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the L7 Policy. A valid value is true (UP) or false (DOWN).

description.Description: Human-readable description for the L7 Policy.

listener_id.Description: The Listener on which the L7 Policy will be associated with. Changing this creates a new L7 Policy.

name.Description: Human-readable name for the L7 Policy. Does not have to be unique.

position.Description: The position of this policy on the listener. Positions start at 1.

redirect_pool_id.Description: Requests matching this policy will be redirected to the pool with this ID. Only valid if action is REDIRECT\_TO\_POOL.

redirect_url.Description: Requests matching this policy will be redirected to this URL. Only valid if action is REDIRECT\_TO\_URL.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Loadbalancer client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new L7 Policy.

vkcs_lb_l7rule.Description: Manages a L7 Rule resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the L7 Rule. A valid value is true (UP) or false (DOWN).

compare_type.Description: The comparison type for the L7 rule - can either be CONTAINS, STARTS\_WITH, ENDS_WITH, EQUAL_TO or REGEX

invert.Description: When true the logic of the rule is inverted. For example, with invert true, equal to would become not equal to. Default is false.

key.Description: The key to use for the comparison. For example, the name of the cookie to evaluate. Valid when `type` is set to COOKIE or HEADER.

l7policy_id.Description: The ID of the L7 Policy to query. Changing this creates a new L7 Rule.

listener_id.Description: The ID of the Listener owning this resource.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Loadbalancer client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new L7 Rule.

type.Description: The L7 Rule type - can either be COOKIE, FILE\_TYPE, HEADER, HOST\_NAME or PATH.

value.Description: The value to use for the comparison. For example, the file type to compare.

vkcs_lb_listener.Description: Manages a listener resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the Listener. A valid value is true (UP) or false (DOWN).

allowed_cidrs.Description: A list of CIDR blocks that are permitted to connect to this listener, denying all other source addresses. If not present, defaults to allow all.

connection_limit.Description: The maximum number of connections allowed for the Listener.

default_pool_id.Description: The ID of the default pool with which the Listener is associated.

default_tls_container_ref.Description: A reference to a Keymanager Secrets container which stores TLS information. This is required if the protocol is `TERMINATED_HTTPS`.

description.Description: Human-readable description for the Listener.

insert_headers.Description: The list of key value pairs representing headers to insert into the request before it is sent to the backend members. Changing this updates the headers of the existing listener.

loadbalancer_id.Description: The load balancer on which to provision this Listener. Changing this creates a new Listener.

name.Description: Human-readable name for the Listener. Does not have to be unique.

protocol.Description: The protocol - can either be TCP, HTTP, HTTPS, TERMINATED_HTTPS, UDP. Changing this creates a new Listener.

protocol_port.Description: The port on which to listen for client traffic. Changing this creates a new Listener.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Loadbalancer client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new Listener.

sni_container_refs.Description: A list of references to Keymanager Secrets containers which store SNI information.

timeout_client_data.Description: The client inactivity timeout in milliseconds.

timeout_member_connect.Description: The member connection timeout in milliseconds.

timeout_member_data.Description: The member inactivity timeout in milliseconds.

timeout_tcp_inspect.Description: The time in milliseconds, to wait for additional TCP packets for content inspection.

vkcs_lb_loadbalancer.Description: Manages a loadbalancer resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the Loadbalancer. A valid value is true (UP) or false (DOWN).

availability_zone.Description: The availability zone of the Loadbalancer. Changing this creates a new loadbalancer.

description.Description: Human-readable description for the Loadbalancer.

name.Description: Human-readable name for the Loadbalancer. Does not have to be unique.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Loadbalancer client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new LB loadbalancer.

security_group_ids.Deprecated: This argument is deprecated, please do not use it
security_group_ids.Description: A list of security group IDs to apply to the loadbalancer. The security groups must be specified by ID and not name (as opposed to how they are configured with the Compute Instance). ***Deprecated*** This argument is deprecated, please do not use it.

tags.Description: A list of simple strings assigned to the loadbalancer.

vip_address.Description: The ip address of the load balancer. Changing this creates a new loadbalancer.

vip_network_id.Description: The network on which to allocate the Loadbalancer's address. A tenant can only create Loadbalancers on networks authorized by policy (e.g. networks that belong to them or networks that are shared).  Changing this creates a new loadbalancer.

vip_port_id.Description: The port UUID that the loadbalancer will use. Changing this creates a new loadbalancer.

vip_subnet_id.Description: The subnet on which to allocate the Loadbalancer's address. A tenant can only create Loadbalancers on networks authorized by policy (e.g. networks that belong to them or networks that are shared).  Changing this creates a new loadbalancer.

vkcs_lb_member.Description: Manages a member resource within VKCS.

address.Description: The IP address of the member to receive traffic from the load balancer. Changing this creates a new member.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the member. A valid value is true (UP) or false (DOWN). Defaults to true.

name.Description: Human-readable name for the member.

pool_id.Description: The id of the pool that this member will be assigned to. Changing this creates a new member.

protocol_port.Description: The port on which to listen for client traffic. Changing this creates a new member.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Loadbalancer client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new member.

subnet_id.Description: The subnet in which to access the member. Changing this creates a new member.

weight.Description: A positive integer value that indicates the relative portion of traffic that this member should receive from the pool. For example, a member with a weight of 10 receives five times as much traffic as a member with a weight of 2. Defaults to 1.

member.Description: A set of dictionaries containing member parameters. The structure is described below.

address.Description: The IP address of the members to receive traffic from the load balancer.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the member. A valid value is true (UP) or false (DOWN). Defaults to true.

backup.Description: A bool that indicates whether the member is backup.

id.Description: The unique ID for the member.

name.Description: Human-readable name for the member.

protocol_port.Description: The port on which to listen for client traffic.

subnet_id.Description: The subnet in which to access the member.

weight.Description: A positive integer value that indicates the relative portion of traffic that this members should receive from the pool. For example, a member with a weight of 10 receives five times as much traffic as a member with a weight of 2. Defaults to 1.

pool_id.Description: The id of the pool that members will be assigned to. Changing this creates a new members resource.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Loadbalancer client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new members resource.

vkcs_lb_monitor.Description: Manages a monitor resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the monitor. A valid value is true (UP) or false (DOWN).

delay.Description: The time, in seconds, between sending probes to members.

expected_codes.Description: Required for HTTP(S) types. Expected HTTP codes for a passing HTTP(S) monitor. You can either specify a single status like "200", or a range like "200-202".

http_method.Description: Required for HTTP(S) types. The HTTP method used for requests by the monitor. If this attribute is not specified, it defaults to "GET".

max_retries.Description: Number of permissible ping failures before changing the member's status to INACTIVE. Must be a number between 1 and 10.

max_retries_down.Description: Number of permissible ping failures befor changing the member's status to ERROR. Must be a number between 1 and 10. Changing this updates the max_retries_down of the existing monitor.

name.Description: The Name of the Monitor.

pool_id.Description: The id of the pool that this monitor will be assigned to.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Loadbalancer client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new monitor.

timeout.Description: Maximum number of seconds for a monitor to wait for a ping reply before it times out. The value must be less than the delay value.

type.Description: The type of probe, which is PING, TCP, HTTP, HTTPS, TLS-HELLO or UDP-CONNECT, that is sent by the load balancer to verify the member state. Changing this creates a new monitor.

url_path.Description: Required for HTTP(S) types. URI path that will be accessed if monitor type is HTTP or HTTPS.

vkcs_lb_pool.Description: Manages a pool resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the pool. A valid value is true (UP) or false (DOWN).

description.Description: Human-readable description for the pool.

lb_method.Description: The load balancing algorithm to distribute traffic to the pool's members. Must be one of ROUND_ROBIN, LEAST_CONNECTIONS, SOURCE_IP, or SOURCE_IP_PORT.

listener_id.Description: The Listener on which the members of the pool will be associated with. Changing this creates a new pool. Note:  One of LoadbalancerID or ListenerID must be provided.

loadbalancer_id.Description: The load balancer on which to provision this pool. Changing this creates a new pool. Note: One of LoadbalancerID or ListenerID must be provided.

name.Description: Human-readable name for the pool.

persistence.Description: Omit this field to prevent session persistence. Indicates whether connections in the same session will be processed by the same Pool member or not. Changing this creates a new pool.

cookie_name.Description: The name of the cookie if persistence mode is set appropriately. Required if `type = APP_COOKIE`.

type.Description: The type of persistence mode. The current specification supports SOURCE_IP, HTTP_COOKIE, and APP_COOKIE.

protocol.Description: The protocol - can either be TCP, HTTP, HTTPS, PROXY, or UDP. Changing this creates a new pool.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Loadbalancer client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new pool.

vkcs_networking_floatingip.Description: Manages a floating IP resource within VKCS that can be used for load balancers.

address.Description: The actual floating IP address itself.

description.Description: Human-readable description for the floating IP.

fixed_ip.Description: Fixed IP of the port to associate with this floating IP. Required if the port has multiple fixed IPs.

pool.Description: The name of the pool from which to obtain the floating IP. Changing this creates a new floating IP.

port_id.Description: ID of an existing port with at least one IP address to associate with this floating IP.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create a floating IP that can be used with another networking resource, such as a load balancer. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new floating IP (which may or may not have a different address).

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

subnet_id.Description: The subnet ID of the floating IP pool. Specify this if the floating IP network has multiple subnets.

subnet_ids.Description: A list of external subnet IDs to try over each to allocate a floating IP address. If a subnet ID in a list has exhausted floating IP pool, the next subnet ID will be tried. This argument is used only during the resource creation. Conflicts with a `subnet_id` argument.

vkcs_networking_floatingip_associate.Description: Associates a floating IP to a port. This is useful for situations where you have a pre-allocated floating IP or are unable to use the `vkcs_networking_floatingip` resource to create a floating IP.

fixed_ip.Description: One of the port's IP addresses.

floating_ip.Description: IP Address of an existing floating IP.

port_id.Description: ID of an existing port with at least one IP address to associate with this floating IP.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create a floating IP that can be used with another networking resource, such as a load balancer. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new floating IP (which may or may not have a different address).

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

vkcs_networking_network.Description: Manages a network resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the network. Acceptable values are "true" and "false". Changing this value updates the state of the existing network.

all_tags.Description: The collection of tags assigned on the network, which have been explicitly and implicitly added.

description.Description: Human-readable description of the network. Changing this updates the name of the existing network.

name.Description: The name of the network. Changing this updates the name of the existing network.

port_security_enabled.Description: Whether to explicitly enable or disable port security on the network. Port Security is usually enabled by default, so omitting this argument will usually result in a value of "true". Setting this explicitly to `false` will disable port security. Valid values are `true` and `false`.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create a network. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new network.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

tags.Description: A set of string tags for the network.

vkcs_services_access.Description: Whether VKCS services access is enabled. This feature should be enabled globally for your project. Access can be enabled for new or existing networks, but cannot be disabled for existing networks. Valid values are `true` and `false`.

vkcs_networking_port.Description: Manages a port resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: Administrative up/down status for the port (must be `true` or `false` if provided). Changing this updates the `admin_state_up` of an existing port.

all_fixed_ips.Description: The collection of Fixed IP addresses on the port in the order returned by the Network v2 API.

all_security_group_ids.Description: The collection of Security Group IDs on the port which have been explicitly and implicitly added.

all_tags.Description: The collection of tags assigned on the port, which have been explicitly and implicitly added.

allowed_address_pairs.Description: An IP/MAC Address pair of additional IP addresses that can be active on this port. The structure is described below.

description.Description: Human-readable description of the port. Changing this updates the `description` of an existing port.

device_id.Description: The ID of the device attached to the port. Changing this creates a new port.

device_owner.Description: The device owner of the port. Changing this creates a new port.

dns_assignment.Description: The list of maps representing port DNS assignments.

extra_dhcp_option.Description: An extra DHCP option that needs to be configured on the port. The structure is described below. Can be specified multiple times.

name.Description: Name of the DHCP option.

fixed_ip.Description: (Conflicts with `no_fixed_ip`) An array of desired IPs for this port. The structure is described below.

ip_address.Description: IP address desired in the subnet for this port. If you don't specify `ip_address`, an available IP address from the specified subnet will be allocated to this port. This field will not be populated if it is left blank or omitted. To retrieve the assigned IP address, use the `all_fixed_ips` attribute.

subnet_id.Description: Subnet in which to allocate IP address for this port.

mac_address.Description: Specify a specific MAC address for the port. Changing this creates a new port.

name.Description: A unique name for the port. Changing this updates the `name` of an existing port.

network_id.Description: The ID of the network to attach the port to. Changing this creates a new port.

no_fixed_ip.Description: (Conflicts with `fixed_ip`) Create a port with no fixed IP address. This will also remove any fixed IPs previously set on a port. `true` is the only valid value for this argument.

no_security_groups.Description: (Conflicts with `security_group_ids`) If set to `true`, then no security groups are applied to the port. If set to `false` and no `security_group_ids` are specified, then the port will yield to the default behavior of the Networking service, which is to usually apply the "default" security group.

port_security_enabled.Description: Whether to explicitly enable or disable port security on the port. Port Security is usually enabled by default, so omitting argument will usually result in a value of `true`. Setting this explicitly to `false` will disable port security. In order to disable port security, the port must not have any security groups. Valid values are `true` and `false`.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create a port. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new port.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

security_group_ids.Description: (Conflicts with `no_security_groups`) A list of security group IDs to apply to the port. The security groups must be specified by ID and not name (as opposed to how they are configured with the Compute Instance).

tags.Description: A set of string tags for the port.

vkcs_networking_port_secgroup_associate.Description:
Manages a port's security groups within VKCS. Useful, when the port was created not by Terraform. It should not be used, when the port was created directly within Terraform.

When the resource is deleted, Terraform doesn't delete the port, but unsets the list of user defined security group IDs.  However, if `enforce` is set to `true` and the resource is deleted, Terraform will remove all assigned security group IDs.

all_security_group_ids.Description: The collection of Security Group IDs on the port which have been explicitly and implicitly added.

enforce.Description: Whether to replace or append the list of security groups, specified in the `security_group_ids`. Defaults to `false`.

port_id.Description: An UUID of the port to apply security groups to.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the networking client. A networking client is needed to manage a port. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new resource.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

security_group_ids.Description: A list of security group IDs to apply to the port. The security groups must be specified by ID and not name (as opposed to how they are configured with the Compute Instance).

vkcs_networking_router.Description: Manages a router resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: Administrative up/down status for the router (must be "true" or "false" if provided). Changing this updates the `admin_state_up` of an existing router.

all_tags.Description: The collection of tags assigned on the router, which have been explicitly and implicitly added.

description.Description: Human-readable description for the router.

external_network_id.Description: The network UUID of an external gateway for the router. A router with an external gateway is required if any compute instances or load balancers will be using floating IPs. Changing this updates the external gateway of the router.

name.Description: A unique name for the router. Changing this updates the `name` of an existing router.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the networking client. A networking client is needed to create a router. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new router.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

tags.Description: A set of string tags for the router.

vendor_options.Description: Map of additional vendor-specific options. Supported options are described below.

set_router_gateway_after_create.Description: Boolean to control whether the Router gateway is assigned during creation or updated after creation.

vkcs_networking_router_interface.Description: Manages a router interface resource within VKCS.

port_id.Description: ID of the port this interface connects to. Changing this creates a new router interface.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the networking client. A networking client is needed to create a router. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new router interface.

router_id.Description: ID of the router this interface belongs to. Changing this creates a new router interface.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

subnet_id.Description: ID of the subnet this interface connects to. Changing this creates a new router interface.

vkcs_networking_router_route.Description: Creates a routing entry on a VKCS router.

destination_cidr.Description: CIDR block to match on the packets destination IP. Changing this creates a new routing entry.

next_hop.Description: IP address of the next hop gateway. Changing this creates a new routing entry.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the networking client. A networking client is needed to configure a routing entry on a router. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new routing entry.

router_id.Description: ID of the router this routing entry belongs to. Changing this creates a new routing entry.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

vkcs_networking_secgroup.Description: Manages a security group resource within VKCS.

all_tags.Description: The collection of tags assigned on the security group, which have been explicitly and implicitly added.

delete_default_rules.Description: Whether or not to delete the default egress security rules. This is `false` by default. See the below note for more information.

description.Description: A unique name for the security group.

name.Description: A unique name for the security group.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the networking client. A networking client is needed to create a port. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new security group.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

tags.Description: A set of string tags for the security group.

vkcs_networking_secgroup_rule.Description: Manages a security group rule resource within VKCS.

description.Description: A description of the rule. Changing this creates a new security group rule.

direction.Description: The direction of the rule, valid values are __ingress__ or __egress__. Changing this creates a new security group rule.

ethertype.Deprecated: Only IPv4 can be used as ethertype. This argument is deprecated, please do not use it.
ethertype.Description: The layer 3 protocol type, the only valid value is __IPv4__. Changing this creates a new security group rule. **Note** This argument is deprecated, please do not use it.

port_range_max.Description: The higher part of the allowed port range, valid integer value needs to be between 1 and 65535. Changing this creates a new security group rule.

port_range_min.Description: The lower part of the allowed port range, valid integer value needs to be between 1 and 65535. Changing this creates a new security group rule.

protocol.Description:
The layer 4 protocol type, valid values are following. Changing this creates a new security group rule. This is required if you want to specify a port range.
  * __tcp__
  * __udp__
  * __icmp__
  * __ah__
  * __dccp__
  * __egp__
  * __esp__
  * __gre__
  * __igmp__
  * __ospf__
  * __pgm__
  * __rsvp__
  * __sctp__
  * __udplite__
  * __vrrp__

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the networking client. A networking client is needed to create a port. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new security group rule.

remote_group_id.Description: The remote group id, the value needs to be an ID of a security group in the same tenant. Changing this creates a new security group rule. **Note**: Only one of `remote_group_id` or `remote_ip_prefix` may be set.

remote_ip_prefix.Description: The remote CIDR, the value needs to be a valid CIDR (i.e. 192.168.0.0/16). Changing this creates a new security group rule. **Note**: Only one of `remote_group_id` or `remote_ip_prefix` may be set.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

security_group_id.Description: The security group id the rule should belong to, the value needs to be an ID of a security group in the same tenant. Changing this creates a new security group rule.

vkcs_networking_subnet.Description: Manages a subnet resource within VKCS.

all_tags.Description: The collection of ags assigned on the subnet, which have been explicitly and implicitly added.

allocation_pool.Description: A block declaring the start and end range of the IP addresses available for use with DHCP in this subnet. Multiple `allocation_pool` blocks can be declared, providing the subnet with more than one range of IP addresses to use with DHCP. However, each IP range must be from the same CIDR that the subnet is part of. The `allocation_pool` block is documented below.

cidr.Description: CIDR representing IP range for this subnet, based on IP version. You can omit this option if you are creating a subnet from a subnet pool.

description.Description: Human-readable description of the subnet. Changing this updates the name of the existing subnet.

dns_nameservers.Description: An array of DNS name server names used by hosts in this subnet. Changing this updates the DNS name servers for the existing subnet.

enable_dhcp.Description: The administrative state of the network. Acceptable values are "true" and "false". Changing this value enables or disables the DHCP capabilities of the existing subnet. Defaults to true.

gateway_ip.Description: Default gateway used by devices in this subnet. Leaving this blank and not setting `no_gateway` will cause a default gateway of `.1` to be used. Changing this updates the gateway IP of the existing subnet.

name.Description: The name of the subnet. Changing this updates the name of the existing subnet.

network_id.Description: The UUID of the parent network. Changing this creates a new subnet.

no_gateway.Description: Do not set a gateway IP on this subnet. Changing this removes or adds a default gateway IP of the existing subnet.

prefix_length.Description: The prefix length to use when creating a subnet from a subnet pool. The default subnet pool prefix length that was defined when creating the subnet pool will be used if not provided. Changing this creates a new subnet.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create a subnet. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new subnet.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

subnetpool_id.Description: The ID of the subnetpool associated with the subnet.

tags.Description: A set of string tags for the subnet.

vkcs_networking_subnet_route.Description: Creates a routing entry on a VKCS subnet.

destination_cidr.Description: CIDR block to match on the packets destination IP. Changing this creates a new routing entry.

next_hop.Description: IP address of the next hop gateway. Changing this creates a new routing entry.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the networking client. A networking client is needed to configure a routing entry on a subnet. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new routing entry.

sdn.Description: SDN to use for this resource. Must be one of following: "neutron", "sprut". Default value is "neutron".

subnet_id.Description: ID of the subnet this routing entry belongs to. Changing this creates a new routing entry.

vkcs_publicdns_record.Description:
Manages a public DNS zone record resource within VKCS. **New since v.0.2.0**.
**Note:** Although some arguments are marked as optional, it is actually required to set values for them depending on record \"type\". Use this map to get information about which arguments you have to set: | Record type | Required arguments | | ----------- | ------------------ | | A | ip | | AAAA | ip | | CNAME | name, content | | MX | priority, content | | NS | content | | SRV | service, proto, priority, weight, host, port | | TXT | content |

full_name.Description: The full name of the SRV record.

host.Description: The domain name of the target host.

ip.Description: The IP address of the record. It should be IPv4 for record of type "A" and IPv6 for record of type "AAAA".

name.Description: The name of the record.

port.Description: The port on the target host of the service.

priority.Description: The priority of the record's server.

proto.Description: The name of the desired protocol.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the V2 Public DNS client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new record.

service.Description: The name of the desired service.

ttl.Description: The time to live of the record.

type.Description: The type of the record. Must be one of following: "A", "AAAA", "CNAME", "MX", "NS", "SRV", "TXT".

weight.Description: The relative weight of the record's server.

zone_id.Description: The ID of the zone to attach the record to.

vkcs_publicdns_zone.Description: Manages a public DNS record resource within VKCS. **New since v.0.2.0**.

admin_email.Description: The admin email of the zone SOA.

expire.Description: The expire time of the zone SOA.

primary_dns.Description: The primary DNS of the zone SOA.

refresh.Description: The refresh time of the zone SOA.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the V2 Public DNS client. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new zone.

retry.Description: The retry time of the zone SOA.

serial.Description: The serial number of the zone SOA.

ttl.Description: The TTL (time to live) of the zone SOA.

zone.Description: The name of the zone. **Changes this creates a new zone**.

vkcs_sharedfilesystem_securityservice.Description:
Use this resource to configure a security service.

~> **Note:** All arguments including the security service password will be stored in the raw state as plain-text. [Read more about sensitive data in state](/docs/state/sensitive-data.html).

A security service stores configuration information for clients for authentication and authorization (AuthN/AuthZ). For example, a share server will be the client for an existing service such as LDAP, Kerberos, or Microsoft Active Directory.

description.Description: The human-readable description for the security service. Changing this updates the description of the existing security service.

dns_ip.Description: The security service DNS IP address that is used inside the tenant network.

name.Description: The name of the security service. Changing this updates the name of the existing security service.

password.Description: The user password, if you specify a user.

project_id.Description: The owner of the Security Service.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Shared File System client. A Shared File System client is needed to create a security service. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new security service.

server.Description: The security service host name or IP address.

type.Description: The security service type - can either be active\_directory, kerberos or ldap.  Changing this updates the existing security service.

user.Description: The security service user or group name that is used by the tenant.

vkcs_sharedfilesystem_share.Description: Use this resource to configure a share.

all_metadata.Description: The map of metadata, assigned on the share, which has been explicitly and implicitly added.

availability_zone.Description: The share availability zone. Changing this creates a new share.

description.Description: The human-readable description for the share. Changing this updates the description of the existing share.

export_location_path.Description: The export location path of the share. **New since v.0.1.15**.

name.Description: The name of the share. Changing this updates the name of the existing share.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Shared File System client. A Shared File System client is needed to create a share. Changing this creates a new share.

share_network_id.Description: The UUID of the share network.

share_proto.Description: The share protocol - can either be NFS, CIFS, CEPHFS, GLUSTERFS, HDFS or MAPRFS. Changing this creates a new share.

share_server_id.Description: The UUID of the share server.

share_type.Description: The share type name. If you omit this parameter, the default share type is used.

size.Description: The share size, in GBs. The requested share size cannot be greater than the allowed GB quota. Changing this resizes the existing share.

snapshot_id.Description: The UUID of the share's base snapshot. Changing this creates a new share.

vkcs_sharedfilesystem_share_access.Description:
Use this resource to control the share access lists.

~> **Important Security Notice** The access key assigned by this resource will be stored *unencrypted* in your Terraform state file. If you use this resource in production, please make sure your state file is sufficiently protected. [Read more about sensitive data in state](https://www.terraform.io/docs/language/state/sensitive-data.html).

access_level.Description: The access level to the share. Can either be `rw` or `ro`.

access_to.Description: The value that defines the access. Can either be an IP address or a username verified by configured Security Service of the Share Network.

access_type.Description: The access rule type. Can either be an ip, user, cert, or cephx.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Shared File System client. A Shared File System client is needed to create a share access. Changing this creates a new share access.

share_id.Description: The UUID of the share to which you are granted access.

vkcs_sharedfilesystem_sharenetwork.Description:
Use this resource to configure a share network.

A share network stores network information that share servers can use when shares are created.

description.Description: The human-readable description for the share network. Changing this updates the description of the existing share network.

name.Description: The name for the share network. Changing this updates the name of the existing share network.

neutron_net_id.Description: The UUID of a neutron network when setting up or updating a share network. Changing this updates the existing share network if it's not used by shares.

neutron_subnet_id.Description: The UUID of the neutron subnet when setting up or updating a share network. Changing this updates the existing share network if it's not used by shares.

project_id.Description: The owner of the Share Network.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Shared File System client. A Shared File System client is needed to create a share network. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new share network.

security_service_ids.Description: The list of security service IDs to associate with the share network. The security service must be specified by ID and not name.

vkcs_vpnaas_endpoint_group.Description: Manages an Endpoint Group resource within VKCS.

description.Description: The human-readable description for the group. Changing this updates the description of the existing group.

endpoints.Description: List of endpoints of the same type, for the endpoint group. The values will depend on the type. Changing this creates a new group.

name.Description: The name of the group. Changing this updates the name of the existing group.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create an endpoint group. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new group.

type.Description: The type of the endpoints in the group. A valid value is subnet, cidr, network, router, or vlan. Changing this creates a new group.

vkcs_vpnaas_ike_policy.Description: Manages a IKE policy resource within VKCS.

auth_algorithm.Description: The authentication hash algorithm. Valid values are sha1, sha256, sha384, sha512. Default is sha1. Changing this updates the algorithm of the existing policy.

description.Description: The human-readable description for the policy. Changing this updates the description of the existing policy.

encryption_algorithm.Description: The encryption algorithm. Valid values are 3des, aes-128, aes-192 and so on. The default value is aes-128. Changing this updates the existing policy.

ike_version.Description: The IKE mode. A valid value is v1 or v2. Default is v1. Changing this updates the existing policy.

lifetime.Description: The lifetime of the security association. Consists of Unit and Value.

units.Description: The units for the lifetime of the security association. Can be either seconds or kilobytes. Default is seconds.

value.Description: The value for the lifetime of the security association. Must be a positive integer. Default is 3600.

name.Description: The name of the policy. Changing this updates the name of the existing policy.

pfs.Description: The perfect forward secrecy mode. Valid values are Group2, Group5 and Group14. Default is Group5. Changing this updates the existing policy.

phase1_negotiation_mode.Description: The IKE mode. A valid value is main, which is the default. Changing this updates the existing policy.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create a VPN service. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new service.

vkcs_vpnaas_ipsec_policy.Description: Manages a IPSec policy resource within VKCS.

auth_algorithm.Description: The authentication hash algorithm. Valid values are sha1, sha256, sha384, sha512. Default is sha1. Changing this updates the algorithm of the existing policy.

description.Description: The human-readable description for the policy. Changing this updates the description of the existing policy.

encapsulation_mode.Description: The encapsulation mode. Valid values are tunnel and transport. Default is tunnel. Changing this updates the existing policy.

encryption_algorithm.Description: The encryption algorithm. Valid values are 3des, aes-128, aes-192 and so on. The default value is aes-128. Changing this updates the existing policy.

lifetime.Description: The lifetime of the security association. Consists of Unit and Value.

units.Description: The units for the lifetime of the security association. Can be either seconds or kilobytes. Default is seconds.

value.Description: The value for the lifetime of the security association. Must be a positive integer. Default is 3600.

name.Description: The name of the policy. Changing this updates the name of the existing policy.

pfs.Description: The perfect forward secrecy mode. Valid values are Group2, Group5 and Group14. Default is Group5. Changing this updates the existing policy.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create an IPSec policy. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new policy.

transform_protocol.Description: The transform protocol. Valid values are ESP, AH and AH-ESP. Changing this updates the existing policy. Default is ESP.

vkcs_vpnaas_service.Description: Manages a VPN service resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the resource. Can either be up(true) or down(false). Changing this updates the administrative state of the existing service.

description.Description: The human-readable description for the service. Changing this updates the description of the existing service.

external_v4_ip.Description: The read-only external (public) IPv4 address that is used for the VPN service.

external_v6_ip.Description: The read-only external (public) IPv6 address that is used for the VPN service.

name.Description: The name of the service. Changing this updates the name of the existing service.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create a VPN service. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new service.

router_id.Description: The ID of the router. Changing this creates a new service.

status.Description: Indicates whether IPsec VPN service is currently operational. Values are ACTIVE, DOWN, BUILD, ERROR, PENDING_CREATE, PENDING_UPDATE, or PENDING_DELETE.

subnet_id.Description: SubnetID is the ID of the subnet. Default is null.

vkcs_vpnaas_site_connection.Description: Manages a IPSec site connection resource within VKCS.

admin_state_up.Description: The administrative state of the resource. Can either be up(true) or down(false). Changing this updates the administrative state of the existing connection.

description.Description: The human-readable description for the connection. Changing this updates the description of the existing connection.

dpd.Description: A dictionary with dead peer detection (DPD) protocol controls.

action.Description: The dead peer detection (DPD) action. A valid value is clear, hold, restart, disabled, or restart-by-peer. Default value is hold.

interval.Description: The dead peer detection (DPD) interval, in seconds. A valid value is a positive integer. Default is 30.

timeout.Description: The dead peer detection (DPD) timeout in seconds. A valid value is a positive integer that is greater than the DPD interval value. Default is 120.

ikepolicy_id.Description: The ID of the IKE policy. Changing this creates a new connection.

initiator.Description: A valid value is response-only or bi-directional. Default is bi-directional.

ipsecpolicy_id.Description: The ID of the IPsec policy. Changing this creates a new connection.

local_ep_group_id.Description: The ID for the endpoint group that contains private subnets for the local side of the connection. You must specify this parameter with the peer_ep_group_id parameter unless in backward- compatible mode where peer_cidrs is provided with a subnet_id for the VPN service. Changing this updates the existing connection.

local_id.Description: An ID to be used instead of the external IP address for a virtual router used in traffic between instances on different networks in east-west traffic. Most often, local ID would be domain name, email address, etc. If this is not configured then the external IP address will be used as the ID.

mtu.Description: The maximum transmission unit (MTU) value to address fragmentation. Minimum value is 68 for IPv4, and 1280 for IPv6.

name.Description: The name of the connection. Changing this updates the name of the existing connection.

peer_address.Description: The peer gateway public IPv4 or IPv6 address or FQDN.

peer_cidrs.Description: Unique list of valid peer private CIDRs in the form < net_address > / < prefix >.

peer_ep_group_id.Description: The ID for the endpoint group that contains private CIDRs in the form < net_address > / < prefix > for the peer side of the connection. You must specify this parameter with the local_ep_group_id parameter unless in backward-compatible mode where peer_cidrs is provided with a subnet_id for the VPN service.

peer_id.Description: The peer router identity for authentication. A valid value is an IPv4 address, IPv6 address, e-mail address, key ID, or FQDN. Typically, this value matches the peer_address value. Changing this updates the existing policy.

psk.Description: The pre-shared key. A valid value is any string.

region.Description: The region in which to obtain the Networking client. A Networking client is needed to create an IPSec site connection. If omitted, the `region` argument of the provider is used. Changing this creates a new site connection.

vpnservice_id.Description: The ID of the VPN service. Changing this creates a new connection.

cloud_containers_api_version.Description:
Cloud Containers API version to use.
_NOTE_ Only for custom VKCS deployments.

project_id.Description: The ID of Project to login with.

region.Description: A region to use.

user_domain_id.Description: The id of the domain where the user resides.

user_domain_name.Description: The name of the domain where the user resides.
